1
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:51,200
<i>In the end, you chose me.</i>

2
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,960
You've got such a mouth.
Let me teach you a lesson.

3
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,120
A boy!

4
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,920
We got a boy!

5
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,440
If you want to quit your job
and start your own company, you can.

6
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:07,760
<i>Then you deserve a reward.</i>

7
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,480
I can't. I can't do it.

8
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:18,920
I can't do it.

9
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,600
- Nueng.
- I can't.

10
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,560
- Nueng.
- What do I do?

11
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,160
- What do I do?
- Nueng.

12
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,280
- I'm here.
- How am I supposed to live?

13
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,120
It's okay.

14
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:30,760
You're okay.

15
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,440
Let's take deep breaths together, okay?

16
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:35,080
Take a deep breath.

17
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:38,320
I can't clean up the vase.

18
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,920
It's okay. I'll clean it up for you.

19
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,360
Do you want to take your medicine?

20
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,360
Medicine? Take medicine?

21
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,880
No, I can't.

22
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,960
Phupha's here. I can't take it.

23
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:54,400
Oon, can you make her
something sweet to drink, please?

24
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,680
Then how am I supposed
to raise him properly?

25
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,320
I can't take medicine.

26
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:01,400
- Try touching your baby.
- I can't do anything.

27
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:04,200
Touch your baby. Touch your baby.

28
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,520
Can you feel Phupha?

29
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,040
- Can you feel him?
- Yeah.

30
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,840
Phupha's moving.

31
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,400
I'm sorry. Mommy's sorry.

32
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:23,640
Mommy can't take care of you properly.

33
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:26,080
I'm sorry. I can't do it.

34
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,240
I can't raise you well.

35
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,640
It's okay, Nueng. Take a deep breath.

36
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,000
Deep breaths.

37
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,280
Breathe with me, okay?

38
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,040
Alright.

39
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,720
Here's the sweet drink.

40
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,880
Thank you.

41
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,440
Take a few sips.

42
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:42,720
Just a little.

43
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,680
Good job. You're doing great.

44
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,000
Alright.

45
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,640
Breathe in. Take a deep breath.

46
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,520
One, two,

47
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,120
three.

48
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:08,120
Hold it. One,

49
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,080
two,

50
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,320
three,

51
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,280
four.

52
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,960
Now slowly breathe out.

53
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:25,840
Panic disorder? Since when?

54
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:30,320
Probably around two or three months ago.

55
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,400
Back when I would take Nueng
to her prenatal appointments,

56
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:36,520
she'd get really anxious.
Her hands and feet would go cold,

57
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,440
and her heart would race.

58
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,920
So we consulted a doctor.

59
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,160
But after the physical examination,

60
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,760
nothing seemed physically wrong.

61
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:48,680
So the doctor suggested
we see a psychiatrist instead.

62
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:54,360
That's when we found out
she has panic disorder.

63
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,000
How did she get that?

64
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:03,280
I think the main reason is because
she can't rely on herself right now.

65
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:07,600
Nueng probably planned to move back
to Thailand and start working,

66
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,160
but then her morning sickness
got severe, so she couldn't work.

67
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:14,640
And once she started feeling better,
her belly was already too big.

68
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,399
Moving around became difficult.

69
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,720
Most importantly,

70
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,080
she's scared she won't be a good mother.

71
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,720
I've been living in the same house as her,

72
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,800
but I didn't notice any of this.

73
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,520
I'm sorry, Fun.

74
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,080
It's okay.

75
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:49,760
Didn't you once tell me that
we were going to build a family together?

76
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:53,760
You'd build from the front of the house,
and I'd build from the back.

77
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:57,880
And one day, we'd meet in the middle
and become a complete home.

78
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,880
Our family.

79
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,680
I'm really lucky

80
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,520
to have you as my life partner.

81
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,240
- Oon.
- Hmm?

82
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,720
I think I'm going to resign.

83
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:31,000
Everything in our life right now
feels like it's falling into place.

84
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:35,120
I'm finally about to start doing
what I've always wanted to do.

85
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,640
And most importantly,

86
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:40,720
our house is about
to have a little one too.

87
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:44,440
I'll finally have time
to help take care of Phupha.

88
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,520
Such a planner.

89
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,680
Oon-oon, are you sure you'll be okay?

90
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,120
Maybe I shouldn't go after all.

91
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,600
I'll be fine.

92
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:17,240
Now that I know what's going on
with Nueng, I can handle it.

93
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,160
I survived dealing with you, didn't I?

94
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,840
Oops, that was the voice in my head.

95
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,600
Hey!

96
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,960
Oon-oon, how much cash
do you have left right now?

97
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,080
Cash?

98
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,920
Probably around 500 baht.

99
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:47,040
Then make it last until the end
of the month. I'm not giving you more.

100
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,160
Huh?

101
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,320
Fun, it's only the middle of the month.

102
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,320
I thought you said you could handle it.

103
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,480
Not this.

104
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:58,280
Fun, are you serious?

105
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,880
You're joking, right?

106
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,560
That's all I'm saying. I'm off now.

107
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,920
Five hundred?

108
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,080
Sit here.

109
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,280
Careful. Slowly.

110
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:08,960
- I'll do it for you.
- It's okay. I can do it.

111
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:11,160
I'll do it.

112
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,960
Nueng,

113
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,680
from now on,

114
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,560
if there's anything you can't handle,

115
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:20,160
tell me, and I'll do it for you.

116
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:26,240
No matter what it is, I'll do it.

117
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,480
Okay?

118
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,080
If I had an older sister,

119
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,000
she'd probably be like you.

120
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,440
Older sister is fine.

121
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:30,240
But if you call me grandma again,
you can get out.

122
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,360
Whoa.

123
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,600
SINGLE MOTHER WITH NOWHERE TO TURN

124
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:59,120
STEALS FROM CONVENIENCE STORE
TO KEEP 7-MONTH-OLD BABY ALIVE

125
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,120
Nueng.

126
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,880
Nueng, I'm here.

127
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,600
I'm here.

128
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,040
Nueng.

129
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:31,000
Nueng, Nueng, Nueng.

130
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:34,120
Nueng.

131
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,080
Can you feel this?

132
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,000
This is your hand.

133
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,800
This is your hand.

134
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,280
This is your arm.

135
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:52,360
Your arm. Can you feel it?

136
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,600
Arm…

137
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:00,960
Arm…

138
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,320
Do you want to hold my hand, Nueng?

139
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:35,520
I'm here. I'm right here.

140
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:41,600
Remember what I told you before?

141
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,440
If there's anything you can't handle,

142
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,240
I'll do it for you.

143
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,840
No matter what it is,

144
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,840
I'll take care of it.

145
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,840
Throw it all at me.

146
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,400
Just tell me.

147
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,400
Let me carry it all for you.

148
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,920
Just don't let go of us, okay?

149
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,840
Now let's breathe together.

150
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,520
One,

151
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:29,680
two,

152
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,040
three,

153
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,520
four.

154
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,080
Hold it…

155
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:43,520
One, two,

156
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,680
three,

157
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:51,440
four, five.

158
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,760
What happened?

159
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,680
You couldn't hold it in?

160
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,600
I think my water just broke.

161
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,640
Your water broke?

162
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:15,880
Her water broke! What do we do?

163
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,240
- I'll get the car ready.
- Get the car ready.

164
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,520
- I'll go get the keys.
- No, Fun.

165
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,760
You need to grab the bag.
I'll get the keys myself.

166
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,000
Okay. Hey, Oon.

167
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,440
The key is not there.

168
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,200
Oh, right.

169
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,240
I'm going to get the bag, okay?
Stay right here.

170
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,680
Wait.

171
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:33,680
- Clothes.
- Clothes?

172
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,680
- Okay, okay. Clothes.
- Yeah.

173
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:42,920
- I'm back. Here are the keys.
- Okay.

174
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,840
I got clothes.

175
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,840
Fun, these are your clothes.

176
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,240
I'll go get them. Here, the keys.

177
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,720
Oh.

178
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,960
Oon, bring the other bag too, okay?

179
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:54,880
Okay.

180
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,680
The bag. The other bag.

181
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,680
Here, clothes. Change now.

182
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,960
Wait, wait, wait.

183
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,640
I'll change in the bathroom.

184
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,720
Bathroom.

185
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,240
- Let's go.
- I'll carry this for you.

186
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,080
Oh.

187
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,720
Slowly.

188
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,320
Be careful.

189
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:20,120
No, you can't come in.

190
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,240
Here.

191
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,640
Be careful.

192
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:29,760
Thank you.

193
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,520
Alright. Okay.

194
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,400
Wait. Where's Nueng?

195
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,320
Nueng!

196
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,640
Wait for me. Where are you going?

197
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,080
- You didn't even wait.
- Nueng.

198
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,360
Hold on.

199
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,280
- Nueng.
- Wait.

200
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,080
- I can't.
- Slowly.

201
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,600
- Open the door.
- Wait.

202
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,240
Open the door.

203
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,360
Get in.

204
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:02,320
- Alright.
- Wait!

205
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,280
The bag!

206
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,480
Go get the bag.

207
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,280
The bag.

208
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,000
- Got it.
- Okay, the bag.

209
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,280
We're going now, okay?

210
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,880
Okay. Go.

211
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:23,400
You're doing great, Mommy.
We can see the baby's head now.

212
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,720
Push, okay?

213
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,520
Deep breath, hold it, push.

214
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,880
Nueng's here.

215
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:42,880
How are you feeling?

216
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,640
It hurt like crazy.

217
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,880
But

218
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,840
once I saw my baby's face,

219
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,880
all the pain just disappeared.

220
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:57,360
So this is what they call

221
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,480
"beautiful pain."

222
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:03,960
You did great, Mommy.

223
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,359
Mommy…

224
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:11,440
The baby's here.

225
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,280
He's so tiny.

226
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,800
So cute.

227
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:23,880
Oon, you're supposed
to say "adorably ugly."

228
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:28,480
So adorably ugly, little one.

229
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:34,280
You should try breastfeeding now, okay?
It'll help stimulate milk production.

230
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,280
Okay.

231
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:58,520
The first milk that comes out
after giving birth is called colostrum.

232
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,440
It's the best thing for the baby.

233
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:01,520
I see.

234
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,080
Fun, do you want to hold him?

235
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:52,320
You're so adorably ugly.

236
00:18:56,640 --> 00:19:01,400
Welcome to the family, Phupha.

237
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,920
We finally get to meet you, Phupha.

238
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,760
He's full now.

239
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:30,800
- All full and already sleepy?
- Already sleepy.

240
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,080
He's asleep.

241
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:44,040
- Oon, Oon.
- What's wrong?

242
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:46,720
I don't know what's happening.

243
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,280
I can't breathe. My chest feels tight.

244
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:50,200
You can't breathe?

245
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:52,520
Oon, go get the nurse now.

246
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,000
Hang on.

247
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,720
I'll get the nurse right away.

248
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:57,640
Oon.

249
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:02,000
The patient's having trouble breathing.
Can someone come check on her, please?

250
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:03,120
<i>Yes.</i>

251
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,720
Oon, Fun.

252
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:11,800
I'm here. I'm right here.

253
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:14,800
I'm here.

254
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:35,680
Doctor, the patient in Room 101
is experiencing respiratory distress.

255
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,920
BP 94/62. Heart rate 110.

256
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,400
Oxygen saturation 90 on room air.

257
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:46,280
Yes, Doctor. Oxygen mask with bag at ten
liters per minute. Transferring to ICU.

258
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,040
Nueng.

259
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:03,840
- Oon.
- I'm here.

260
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,520
Take care of Phupha for me.

261
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:18,480
- Nueng.
- Nueng.

262
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:19,480
Nueng!

263
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,720
No pulse. Patient's having cardiac arrest.

264
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,080
Nueng.

265
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:29,200
Nueng.

266
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,000
- Nueng.
- Nueng.

267
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:36,680
- Nueng.
- Nueng.

268
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:41,000
Nueng.

269
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:45,040
Nueng.

270
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:50,000
Excuse us.

271
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,320
She'll be fine.

272
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:02,880
Checking pulse.

273
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,200
No pulse detected.

274
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:07,840
EKG shows V-fib.

275
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,240
Nueng has to be okay.

276
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,120
Prepare to shock.

277
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,520
Defibrillation, 200 joules.

278
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:30,120
Shock. Start CPR.

279
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,560
Prepare defibrillation, 200 joules.

280
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,280
Shock.

281
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:04,320
Are you relatives of Ms. Kanyawee?

282
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,440
Yes.

283
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,920
I'm very sorry for your loss.

284
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,480
The patient passed away

285
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:13,080
at 3.10 p.m. The cause of death

286
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:16,720
is suspected to be
amniotic fluid embolism,

287
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:19,400
which is a severe condition
that progresses very rapidly.

288
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:22,240
Our medical team did everything we could,

289
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:25,040
but unfortunately,
we were unable to save her.

290
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,640
Please accept our condolences.

291
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:35,880
Nueng…

292
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:37,480
Oon…

293
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:41,320
It's not true, right?

294
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,760
It's not true, right, Oon?

295
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,120
Oon.

296
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,280
- Mom.
- What happened?

297
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:20,840
Nueng already gave birth, right?

298
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,920
Nueng…

299
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:31,360
Nueng's dead, Mom.

300
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,200
Nueng…

301
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:47,400
Mom. Mom.

302
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:52,800
Mom.

303
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:00,760
Can we get some ammonia, please?

304
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,520
Thank you.

305
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:10,760
If you need anything,
just call for a nurse, okay?

306
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:19,240
How could this happen?

307
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,240
How did Nueng die?

308
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,280
She…

309
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:29,280
The doctor said
it was an amniotic fluid embolism, Mom.

310
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:30,840
Oh, Nueng…

311
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:35,720
What about the baby? How's the baby?

312
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,760
The baby's safe.
He's in the nursery right now.

313
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:44,320
Nueng, why was your fate so cruel?

314
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,480
Nueng…

315
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,120
Fun,

316
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:00,240
we have to stay strong.

317
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:03,080
We have to do
this one last thing for Nueng.

318
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,240
I'll…

319
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:08,680
handle the temple arrangements.

320
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:12,440
Fun, you take care
of the hospital paperwork.

321
00:26:13,080 --> 00:26:13,920
Nueng…

322
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:15,960
Okay.

323
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:18,520
We'll do this one last thing for Nueng.

324
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:43,000
How can I help you?

325
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:46,400
I wanted to ask…

326
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:51,480
if I'd like the hospital to care for him
during his mother's funeral,

327
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,520
which department should I contact?

328
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:57,600
You can report the details here first,
then contact Medical Records afterward.

329
00:26:58,240 --> 00:26:59,480
This way, please.

330
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,040
I'm going to rest now.

331
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:59,160
Tomorrow, we'll go pick up Phupha.

332
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,080
Fun…

333
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:20,920
There's something
I want to talk to you about.

334
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,000
What is it?

335
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:28,560
I want the two of us to raise Phupha.

336
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:32,960
I feel so attached to him.

337
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:37,320
We've been with him
since he was still in the womb.

338
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,520
I want to take care of him

339
00:28:40,040 --> 00:28:41,880
and watch him grow up.

340
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,840
Can you do this with me?

341
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,880
I feel the same way.

342
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:58,440
To me, Phupha is a precious thing…

343
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:03,560
that Nueng left behind for us.

344
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:08,520
Thank you.

345
00:29:31,120 --> 00:29:32,200
Oh, my goodness.

346
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:36,040
- Baby Phupha is here.
- Phupha, sweetheart.

347
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:44,600
Thank you so much.

348
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:46,080
Thank you.

349
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,040
PHUPHA SRIPITICHOTE
JUNE 5, 2026 - WEIGHT: 2,999 GRAMS

350
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,600
Look at him.

351
00:29:58,720 --> 00:30:00,600
So adorably ugly.

352
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,600
Little Phupha,

353
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:06,080
come stay with Grandma, okay?

354
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,280
Let's go.

355
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:30,200
I think I'll stay here
for another couple of days,

356
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:32,800
then I'll take Phupha back home
with me to Ayutthaya.

357
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,120
Mom.

358
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:37,920
What?

359
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,160
What are you two doing?

360
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:41,040
I…

361
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:46,760
I want to raise Phupha myself.

362
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:52,160
I want to raise Phupha too.

363
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:56,000
How are the two of you going to raise him?
This isn't easy, you know.

364
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:58,440
Raising a newborn is hard.

365
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:01,840
Both of you work outside the house too.

366
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:04,160
At night? Forget it.

367
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:06,080
There's no way you'll get
a full night's sleep,

368
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:08,720
because babies cry constantly.

369
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:13,680
And going out together alone?
Going to dinner? Relaxing?

370
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:15,520
Don't even think about it.

371
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:16,720
You won't have the chance.

372
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:21,480
Can you give us a chance
to take care of Phupha?

373
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:25,240
Please, Mom.

374
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:28,320
We'll prove to you

375
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:30,600
that we really can take care of him.

376
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:32,560
Please, Mom. Please, please.

377
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:35,000
- Please.
- Can you really do it?

378
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:37,200
- Please.
- Please, Mom.

379
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:38,560
I'll think about it first.

380
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:52,680
That works.

381
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,040
Here you go, sweetheart, your milk.

382
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:19,200
Hello, yes.

383
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:24,200
Oh, sure. I'll send the revised draft
via email right away.

384
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:35,440
There we go. All clean and dry now.
You're comfortable again.

385
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,520
You can sleep, Mom.
I'll take care of Phupha.

386
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,280
- Can you handle it?
- Yes.

387
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:09,200
That's right. Hold him.

388
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,920
Let's change your diaper.

389
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:14,360
Fun.

390
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,640
- Yes?
- Did you clean Phupha's belly button yet?

391
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:18,040
His belly button…

392
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:20,880
- Oh, right.
- You have to clean it properly.

393
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:23,000
Otherwise, it could get infected.

394
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:26,280
You have to be careful,
or Phupha could get a stomachache.

395
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:30,160
Here, let me explain.

396
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:33,760
When the umbilical stump is about
to fall off, you have to be extra careful.

397
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:36,080
Come on.

398
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:38,400
There, there.

399
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:39,520
There, there.

400
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,480
Sweetheart.

401
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:45,400
I'm cleaning your little belly button.

402
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:48,160
Didn't they teach this
in the class you attended?

403
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:53,040
They did. I just forgot last night.

404
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:54,920
You didn't get enough sleep, right?

405
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:58,720
I told you already,
raising a baby is exhausting.

406
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:02,040
Go get some rest. I'll handle things here.

407
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,760
Hi, Fun.

408
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:25,760
- Aunt Wi, hello.
- Hello, dear.

409
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,560
How's the little one doing?

410
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,080
He's doing well.

411
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:33,600
If everything's fine,

412
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:35,400
why do you look so down?

413
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:40,239
Aunt Wi, raising a child
really isn't easy at all.

414
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:43,480
I guess you need experience
to be able to do it properly.

415
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,400
You don't need experience at all.

416
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:50,560
Otherwise, how would
first-time parents raise their kids?

417
00:34:50,639 --> 00:34:51,880
Look at me.

418
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:55,840
I raised Pa since she was tiny, since she
was only two months old. Nobody taught me.

419
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:59,320
I watched videos and read books,

420
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:01,680
but in the end, the best thing

421
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:04,680
is to use your heart to raise them.
Trust me.

422
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:07,000
Aunt Wi, you're amazing.

423
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:11,600
Is there some kind of fixed rule
when it comes to raising kids?

424
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:15,360
Absolutely not.
You just follow the child's lead.

425
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:17,680
If they're hungry, you feed them milk.

426
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:19,960
After that, you burp them.

427
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:24,200
If they fart, poop or pee,
you change their diaper.

428
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:27,400
And if they seem uncomfortable,
you check if they have a fever

429
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:29,560
or a stomachache or something.

430
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:30,880
It's not that hard, dear.

431
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:35,000
You just get to know them more every day.
You'll start understanding their signals.

432
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:38,400
It's like a kind of body language
that only the two of you understand.

433
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,840
I want to have that kind of bond too.

434
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:45,360
It'll happen eventually.

435
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,600
You're the one raising the child,
after all,

436
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:50,560
so the bond will naturally form
on its own.

437
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:54,320
Honestly, I don't think
raising a child to adulthood is hard.

438
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:58,800
What's difficult is raising them
to become a good person. Don't you agree?

439
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:01,360
That's true.

440
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,960
That's probably much harder.

441
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:09,720
Oh, Fun, after this,
I won't be home very often anymore.

442
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,400
I'll have to travel back and forth
between Bangkok and Ang Thong

443
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:14,760
because my sister isn't feeling well.

444
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,920
Make sure you lock your doors
and windows properly.

445
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:19,840
Thank you so much, Aunt Wi.

446
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,440
You stay strong too, okay?

447
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:24,840
I hope your sister gets better soon.

448
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:28,520
I should go check on the baby now.
I'll update you if anything happens.

449
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,840
- See you.
- See you. Take care.

450
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,200
See you.

451
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,680
Please receive this blessing.

452
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,720
For those who always
pay respect to their elders,

453
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:33,520
four blessings shall grow.

454
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:36,080
Long life, beauty, happiness

455
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:39,200
and strength. Blessings upon you.

456
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:48,520
Nueng, I've made merit for you now.

457
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:51,160
Don't worry about Phupha.

458
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:54,240
We'll help raise him well.

459
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,800
It's already been 49 days
since Nueng left us.

460
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:20,840
I think we should start
packing up Nueng's belongings soon.

461
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:44,560
AIOON AND PAFUN

462
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,600
- Oon.
- Hmm?

463
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:53,000
Come look at this.

464
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:29,000
<i>To Aioon and Pafun,</i>

465
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:33,800
<i>If you two are reading this letter,</i>

466
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:37,200
<i>then I'm probably no longer in this world.</i>

467
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:41,560
<i>Originally,</i>
<i>I planned to come back, find work</i>

468
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:45,360
<i>and build a small family</i>
<i>with just me and Phupha.</i>

469
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:48,560
<i>But everything fell apart,</i>

470
00:39:48,640 --> 00:39:49,800
<i>completely.</i>

471
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:54,000
<i>My panic disorder never seemed to improve.</i>

472
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,800
<i>It felt like</i>
<i>it would stay with me forever.</i>

473
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,360
<i>Every time I had an episode,</i>

474
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,040
<i>it made me feel like</i>

475
00:40:04,120 --> 00:40:06,400
<i>there might not be a tomorrow.</i>

476
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:09,920
<i>I tried to be strong.</i>

477
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:12,920
<i>I wanted to become</i>
<i>a good mother for Phupha.</i>

478
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:15,880
<i>If I don't get the chance to do that,</i>

479
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:19,000
<i>please take care of Phupha for me.</i>

480
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:20,840
<i>Please take care of him</i>

481
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:25,520
<i>and tell him you love him</i>
<i>and hug him on my behalf too.</i>

482
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:30,280
<i>I know both of you love him</i>
<i>just as much as I do.</i>

483
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:33,400
<i>Thank you</i>

484
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:37,320
<i>for staying by my side, taking care of me,</i>

485
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:41,120
<i>understanding me</i>
<i>and encouraging me all this time.</i>

486
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:43,960
<i>I love you both so much,</i>

487
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:46,680
<i>Aioon, Pafun.</i>

488
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:54,600
NUBNUENG

489
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:09,840
What are you two doing?

490
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:17,800
It's a letter from Nueng.

491
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,720
Did the baby fall asleep already?

492
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:55,960
‪Yeah.

493
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:57,880
Once he was full,
he fell asleep pretty quickly.

494
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:03,240
Then eat while you can.
If he cries, I'll go check on him.

495
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:07,040
Oon.

496
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:09,400
I'm heading home this afternoon.

497
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:12,080
I already asked Priaw to call me a car.

498
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:13,440
‪What?

499
00:43:18,240 --> 00:43:19,120
Mom,

500
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:22,320
can you not go yet? Please don't take
Phupha away. Stay with us a bit longer.

501
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:24,120
- Please, Mom.
- Please, Mom.

502
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:25,640
Please, Mom. Give us another chance.

503
00:43:25,720 --> 00:43:27,520
If I do something wrong,

504
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:31,040
you can scold me. You can even hit me.
Just please don't take Phupha away.

505
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:32,720
- Please.
- I'm begging you.

506
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:33,800
Stop.

507
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:37,600
Did I ever say
I was taking Phupha with me?

508
00:43:38,720 --> 00:43:41,440
I only said I was going home.

509
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,240
- I love you so much, Mom.
- Thank you.

510
00:43:45,320 --> 00:43:48,280
Thank you so much, Mom.

511
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:52,000
There, the baby's crying.

512
00:43:52,080 --> 00:43:53,640
- I'll go check on him myself.
- I'll go.

513
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:55,960
- You barely touched your food.
- It's okay.

514
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:04,040
See?
Having and raising a child isn't easy.

515
00:44:04,120 --> 00:44:08,400
You can't even enjoy a proper meal
or sit peacefully for a while.

516
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:10,960
I know, Mom.

517
00:44:13,320 --> 00:44:15,120
This is my family,

518
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:18,880
the family I've always wanted.

519
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:23,160
No matter what happens,

520
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:26,440
I'll get through it.

521
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:31,000
Good. As long as you understand that.

522
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:36,040
But if it ever becomes too much, tell me.

523
00:44:44,040 --> 00:44:45,600
Thank you, Mom.

524
00:44:45,680 --> 00:44:48,600
Why are you hugging me now?
I'm not even done eating yet.

525
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:49,760
Let go.

526
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:52,720
Look at you.

527
00:44:55,720 --> 00:44:57,480
I love you the most, Mom.

528
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:54,440
Nueng.

529
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:00,480
What are you looking at?

530
00:46:16,760 --> 00:46:17,760
Oon…

531
00:46:20,160 --> 00:46:21,600
Thank you so much

532
00:46:22,480 --> 00:46:24,160
for taking such good care of both me

533
00:46:25,080 --> 00:46:27,080
and Phupha.

534
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:30,200
What are you thanking me for?

535
00:46:31,480 --> 00:46:33,040
I already told you,

536
00:46:33,640 --> 00:46:37,120
if there's ever anything, just tell me.
I'll handle it.

537
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:38,800
No matter what it is--

538
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:40,400
I'll do it for you.

539
00:46:57,320 --> 00:46:58,920
Thank you so much.

540
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:06,320
Please take care of my son for me.

541
00:47:23,680 --> 00:47:25,400
Where are you going?

542
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:30,160
Nueng.

543
00:47:31,720 --> 00:47:32,880
<i>Thank you.</i>

544
00:47:35,080 --> 00:47:38,000
Nueng, Nueng.

545
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:47,160
Nueng.

546
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:49,480
Nueng.

547
00:47:50,960 --> 00:47:52,840
- Nueng.
- Oon.

548
00:48:00,320 --> 00:48:02,400
You were so loud. You woke the baby.

549
00:48:02,480 --> 00:48:04,040
I'll go check on him.

550
00:48:10,960 --> 00:48:14,920
Mommy's here now, sweetheart.

551
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:21,920
I'm gonna change your diaper, okay?

552
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:25,440
I'm gonna change your diaper.

553
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:28,760
You'll feel much more comfortable
after this.

554
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:34,560
It's okay, sweetheart.

555
00:48:34,640 --> 00:48:37,840
Once we change your diaper,
you'll feel all better.

556
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:41,120
Let me see.

557
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:43,640
Let me wipe you clean, okay?
Then you'll be comfy again.

558
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:49,040
Okay.

559
00:48:49,120 --> 00:48:50,040
- Wait a second.
- Okay.

560
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:55,080
I'm wiping you,
so you'll feel comfortable.

561
00:49:02,120 --> 00:49:05,040
Oon, don't scream.
He hasn't finished peeing yet.

562
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:29,240
<i>I can stay home with him.</i>

563
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:30,400
Don't worry.

564
00:49:30,480 --> 00:49:31,400
Are you sure?

565
00:49:31,480 --> 00:49:33,840
Why is your face all messy like this?
What were you two playing with?

566
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:35,040
Aioon!

567
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:37,680
<i>I think some things</i>

568
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:40,360
are just too intense for a child this age.

569
00:49:40,440 --> 00:49:42,680
It hurts here, here

570
00:49:42,760 --> 00:49:44,640
and here too.

571
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:46,560
You have a headache, right?

572
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:52,400
Am I a bad mother, Oon?

573
00:50:22,240 --> 00:50:24,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
